      <p>
        <strong>Why it works for seedlings:</strong> coir provides a fine, moisture-holding base that can support germination when balanced with enough air and drainage.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Watch-outs:</strong> straight coir can stay too wet or too dense in some trays. It also contains little nutrition, so seedlings may need feeding or potting up later.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Best buying use:</strong> choose this as a DIY ingredient, not necessarily as a complete finished mix.
      </p>

